{
  "texts": [
    "On the other hand, the lensing mass distribution can be altered quite drastically with little change in the images.",
    "In fact, as we will see presently, it is possible to modify a lens while keeping lensing observables exactly fixed.",
    "This is the problem of lensing degeneracies.",
    "Let us go back to Fig. 3, and run the light backwards.",
    "That is to say, let us consider a single observer above (at the origin of the rays), and imagine sources scattered over the figure."
  ]
}